Latest on Redness: Concentrations decreased in Pinellas, Manatee and Sarasota
The latest report from the Florida Fish and Wildlife Commission shows a general decrease in Redness concentrations for parts of the Tampa Bay area.
According to the FWC, collar flowering conditions are reported in the areas of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier cities - suggesting reduced concentrations.
In full bloom, the Red River stretches about 130 miles along the coastline from northern Pinellas to southern Lee cities.
Kolle can be found about 10 miles off the coast of Hillsborough city, but at fewer locations compared to last week.
Rooigety is also noted in Pasco city.
Medium concentrations in or near the coast of Pinellas city have been reported in recent weeks concentrates in low to high concentrations near the coast of Hillsborough city, background to high concentrations in Manatee city, background to high concentrations in or near the coast of Pinellas city.
Breathing irritation continues to be reported in Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier cities.
Breathing irritation has not been reported in Northwest Florida in the past week.
